We then define the multiplication for any arbitrary Dedekind cuts \alpha \in  R and \beta \in  R by
\alpha \beta  = \begin {cases}(-\alpha )(-\beta ) & \hbox {if }\alpha <0_{R},\beta <0_{R},\\ -[(-\alpha )\beta ] & \hbox {if }\alpha <0_{R}<\beta \\ -[\alpha \cdot (-\beta )] & \hbox {if }\beta <0_{R}<\alpha . \end {cases}
The product used in each of these cases is the one from Addition of Dedekind cuts satisfies the relevant ordered field axioms.
